16 July
Londen Jan Kent & comp
m sence my last of 13 cur non from you, att which I wonder
because you give mee no account of what passes in the nord,
neither send mee anney remises, which you can doe so easehey
all my remises beenge in cas with you, so pray, lett mee have some
bencfice, there by, for I hope you will not refuse my payement
or what I order
nd in bills att I usance & I am told, that our ostendish convoy will come
for London again in a sphort time, so lett the cottons bee readdy, &
the spa cloathes, addinge some more, as by the inclosed notice, yett
loose no opportunitie, to send mee one pack by the first convoy
for holland, if that sailes before that of ostend buy a pack
to containg 4 depie red clothes of £9 a £9:10 p & 4 ditto of
£t0: 2a p £10, & an other pack to bee assorted with 20 worster
frises of the best sort, yett not excceding 4 p a yeard, a penney
p' o more or less to come by the first convoj for ostend, inclosed
also some patt. & instruction for 2 packes of cloth to bee sent to huse
to be shipped by the first convoyé for holland, I wish the convoyes
from thence were safe over in exspectation to breu passe
remaire on receave here of, please to send mee some patt of the
newest cullours of spo clothes now in lasscon with you for I
dam informed as if there was a new cullour againe, yett all the
demand here is for close mixture hota that the red clothes
must not bee to doch butt to the inclosed patt. & faile not to provi
the blew grayes I rese
Londen Richard Southell
I have yours of 30 may last nod answered for want of occassi
haveinge sont to gand to m de sadelaer your 12 resting crespes, recea
red the of the 4 sold you shall have the account & vallew prere
first exspectinge onley to heve know the charges that are risen theres
att gand, as to the red clothes, I am informed that our convoij from
stend shall come for london againe in a short time, so please
to send by the same a pack to bee assorted with 4 demie p of
s.o if you have no accasion to buy red clothes for others &
what these should cost the dearer so would rather have non
butt t hope you have commissions for other handes that so
you, can send, my assortiment to my desire in exspectation of
your advise to take my measures accordingley remaine
18 July
london Samnel Blewitt
sence my last of 22 past non from you, this ouley for covtert of
the inelosed invoyce of a pack of tjkes, which I have sent pr bridges
this weeck to come for london by the first convoy, if you please
to have itt lett mee have your answer without labse of time en remise

Londen Beniamin gjles
in answer to yours of 16 past this well, that you have adiusted the
two accounts in conformitie, the time is att present so here, that I
deare meddle with no brade, for wee run a great risico in sellinge,
so that I intend to sitt still, t'ill peace come, interim as to tykes
they fold their prise & no hope to buy anney cheaper then
by the inclosed invoyce, of a pack & N3, which I have sent to
bridges to fir cootr to forward by the first convoij for london, if
you pleace to accept there of fors your account shall consigue
to you ou your order, as sureinge you that towards winter they
shall bee dearer, haveinge payd these before I had them, &
are vere the best sorts & best assorted in exspectation of your
answer remaine
